of the \fB<CONFIG>_POSTFIX\fP \%<#\:prop_tgt:<CONFIG>_POSTFIX> target property value as part of the
base name. The default is \fBPOSTFIX:INCLUDE\fP\&.

.sp
Base name of \fBtgt\fP, i.e. \fB$<TARGET_FILE_NAME:tgt>\fP without prefix and
suffix and, optionally, postfix.
For example, if the \fBtgt\fP filename is \fBlibbase_postfix.so\fP, the base name
is:
.INDENT 7.0
.INDENT 3.5
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBbase_postfix\fP for \fB$<TARGET_FILE_BASE_NAME:tgt>\fP or
\fB$<TARGET_FILE_BASE_NAME:tgt,POSTFIX:INCLUDE>\fP\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBbase\fP for \fB$<TARGET_FILE_BASE_NAME:tgt,POSTFIX:EXCLUDE>\fP\&.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
See also the \fBOUTPUT_NAME\fP \%<#\:prop_tgt:OUTPUT_NAME>, \fBARCHIVE_OUTPUT_NAME\fP \%<#\:prop_tgt:ARCHIVE_OUTPUT_NAME>,
